text: Janette Manrara-Škorjanec (born 16 November 1983) is a Cuban-American television presenter, choreographer and professional dancer from Miami, Florida, the United States of America. ==Works== Originally she was a salsa dancer, she learned from her Cuban family. She studied dance from the age of 19. Manrara was best known for her appearances on the American series So You Think You Can Dance and the BBC One celebrity dancing show Strictly Come Dancing. She is married to Slovenian dancer and co-star Aljaž Škorjanec. In June 2021, it was announced that Manrara would co-host the weekday show Strictly Come Dancing: It Takes Two with Rylan Clark-Neal.
